    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 8,
        "summary": "Christ will be as a stone of stumbling and a rock of offense\u2014Seek the Lord, not muttering wizards\u2014Turn to the law and to the testimony for guidance\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 18.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Moreover the Lord said unto me, Take thee a great roll, and write in it with a man's pen concerning Maher-shalal-hash-baz.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 18:1 (1\u201322).",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Writing of.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0an engraving tool of a man.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0To speed to the spoil, he hasteneth the prey.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I took unto me faithful witnesses to record, Uriah the priest, and Zechariah the son of Jeberechiah.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I went unto the prophetess; and she conceived, and bare a son. Then said the Lord to me, Call his name Maher-shalal-hash-baz.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0his wife. Alma 32:23.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 7:3; 8:18 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For before the child shall have knowledge to cry, My father, and my mother, the riches of Damascus and the spoil of Samaria shall be taken away before the king of Assyria.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 7:16.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 18:4.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 15:29.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord spake also unto me again, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Forasmuch as this people refuseth the waters of Shiloah that go softly, and rejoice in Rezin and Remaliah's son;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Neh. 3:15; John 9:7.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 7:1 (1\u20136).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Now therefore, behold, the Lord bringeth up upon them the waters of the river, strong and many, even the king of Assyria, and all his glory: and he shall come up over all his channels, and go over all his banks:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0upon northern Israel first.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 46:7 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 10:12.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall pass through Judah; he shall overflow and go over, he shall reach even to the neck; and the stretching out of his wings shall fill the breadth of thy land, O Immanuel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Assyria will penetrate Judah also.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 30:28.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the land of the future birth of Immanuel.",
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 179
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Associate yourselves, O ye people, and ye shall be broken in pieces; and give ear, all ye of far countries: gird yourselves, and ye shall be broken in pieces; gird yourselves, and ye shall be broken in pieces.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Form alliances.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take counsel together, and it shall come to nought; speak the word, and it shall not stand: for God is with us.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:19; 3:7 (6\u201311).",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Judah (land of Immanuel) will be spared. Ps. 46:7.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Lord spake thus to me with a strong hand, and instructed me that I should not walk in the way of this people, saying,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0in power.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Say ye not, A confederacy, to all them to whom this people shall say, A confederacy; neither fear ye their fear, nor be afraid.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Judah should not rely on secret plots with others for safety.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Sanctify the Lord of hosts himself; and let him be your fear, and let him be your dread.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 872
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall be for a sanctuary; but for a stone of stumbling and for a rock of offence to both the houses of Israel, for a gin and for a snare to the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0security for those who trust Him, but dismay and suffering for unbelievers. Ezek. 11:16 (15\u201321).",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cornerstone.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 21:44 (43\u201345); Luke 2:34; Rom. 9:32 (28\u201333).",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 11:6; 24:10. TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 69:22.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And many among them shall stumble, and fall, and be broken, and be snared, and be taken.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Bind up the testimony, seal the law among my disciples.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 109:46.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seal.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0teachings or doctrine.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will wait upon the Lord, that hideth his face from the house of Jacob, and I will look for him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 32:20.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 54:8 (4\u201310).",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I and the children whom the Lord hath given me are for signs and for wonders in Israel from the Lord of hosts, which dwelleth in mount Zion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0The names of Isaiah and his sons mean respectively: \u201cJehovah saves\u201d; \u201cHe hastens the prey\u201d; and \u201cA remnant shall return.\u201d Isa. 7:3; 8:3. TG\u00a0Symbolism.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And when they shall say unto you, Seek unto them that have familiar spirits, and unto wizards that peep, and that mutter: should not a people seek unto their God? for the living to the dead?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorcery; Spirits, Evil or Unclean.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0sorcerers, soothsayers. TG\u00a0Superstitions.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0on behalf of.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To the law and to the testimony: if they speak not according to this word, it is because there is no light in them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Value of.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the spiritualist mediums (also in vv.\u00a021\u201322).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Light [noun].",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall pass through it, hardly bestead and hungry: and it shall come to pass, that when they shall be hungry, they shall fret themselves, and curse their king and their God, and look upward.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Israel would be taken into captivity because they would not hearken.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blaspheme.",
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 155
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall look unto the earth; and behold trouble and darkness, dimness of anguish; and they shall be driven to darkness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0dark affliction.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}